Ok so we are in a COVID pandemic, Dominoes offers contact less delivery... sounds great! Thats if it were really contactless. If the delivery guy stands at my door demanding to see the card that I used to pay for my order online- then im not sure how this is considered a contact less delivery. The delivery instructions state to leave food at door and keep 6ft distance. Yet the delivery man refused to deliver my fully paid for order. Is it that Harlem, NYC residents are not worth the same safety precautions and delivery instructions that Dominoes promotes when placing orders online??? Until I can make sense of this, I'm staying safe and sticking to Uber Eats where the deliveries are truly contactless.

Summary: Hours listed NOT accurate (despite being a simple fix). Despite normally ordering from here multiple times a week, sadly this location will no longer be a dinner option for my partner and me.  My partner and I usually order carry-out at this location several times a week. Unfortunately, we’ve learned they’re no longer reliable. We tried to order yesterday during their listed hours— order did not go through, plus we walked over there in case it was only an online issue but no luck. We figured the early closure was just due to the holiday so we tried again today— order once again would not go through (after trying 10+ times). We walked over just in time to see them closing up.  I know this is an uncertain time and I want to be understanding, especially since we are very regular customers and love the food. However, we had a similar hiccup with online ordering recently and when we went to the store, we found it was open— the workers there informed us that the manager/owner (don’t remember which) was messing with the online options from his home. So it would be VERY easy for them to go online and change the operating hours. I hate to say it, but if the listed hours aren’t accurate, we simply can’t count on this particular location as a dinner option for the time being. There are very few other late night options currently, and we just can’t be left without dinner due to their unpredictability.

I love Domino's pizza. Am a born and bred New Yorker, formerly a Queens girl, so I know good pizza. Is it as good as Angelo and Al's Pizza in Fresh Meadows or Rays Pizza in Manhattan? No, but it is way better than many of the pizza places around, especially the chains. And, as a vegan who is now on a gluten free, fun-free diet (thanks to Lyme disease), I can still enjoy eating pizza when my family orders in. I get the gluten free crust with robust sauce (the marinara has dairy), mushrooms, olives and no cheese. It's absolutely delicious doused with extra virgin olive oil. Yum! All that and quick delivery too.
